.TH "spi_replace_transfers" 9 "spi_replace_transfers" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spi_replace_transfers \- replace transfers with several transfers and register change with spi_message.resources
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct spi_replaced_transfers *" spi_replace_transfers
.BI "(struct spi_message *msg "  ","
.BI "struct spi_transfer *xfer_first "  ","
.BI "size_t remove "  ","
.BI "size_t insert "  ","
.BI "spi_replaced_release_t release "  ","
.BI "size_t extradatasize "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "msg" 12
the spi_message we work upon
.IP "xfer_first" 12
the first spi_transfer we want to replace
.IP "remove" 12
number of transfers to remove
.IP "insert" 12
the number of transfers we want to insert instead
.IP "release" 12
extra release code necessary in some circumstances
.IP "extradatasize" 12
extra data to allocate (with alignment guarantees
of struct \fIspi_transfer\fP)
.IP "gfp" 12
gfp flags
.SH "RETURN"
pointer to \fIspi_replaced_transfers\fP,
PTR_ERR(...) in case of errors.
